Having dry skin is bad  but when  cracked heels come into the picture, walking around won’t be so fun anymore. But the good news is treating cracked hills isn’t so complicated now that there are a lot of home remedies available so that you don’t get to spend so much  money in keeping your feet in tip top shape. While dry skin is the major culprit when it comes to  causes of cracked heels. According to institute for preventive foot health prolonged standing, especially on hard floor, wearing shoes with open backs, having calluses etc can cause your heels to crack although in some cases the cracks are minor, but in severe cases it might lead to bleeding which might lead to an infection. That’s why its important you take care of the problem early. Here are tips on how to appease your cracked heel and give them the much needed relief.